HEADWORD: Alkermes
<hw>Al*ker"mes</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>al-qirmiz</ets> kermes. See <er>Kermes</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old
Pharmacy)</fld> <def>A compound cordial, in the form of a confection,
deriving its name from the kermes insect, its principal
ingredient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

